The paper focuses on a mobile wireless sensor network (MWSN) and addresses the issues of energy consumption and sensing coverage. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Robotics (cs.RO), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Information Theory (cs.IT). However, since the paper deals with the deployment of mobile sensors, we can eliminate cs.IT as a likely sub-category. Among the remaining four sub-categories, cs.MA and cs.RO are the most likely since they deal with mobile agents and robots. cs.NI is also a possibility since it deals with wireless networks, while cs.SY deals with control and optimization, which are relevant to the problem of sensor deployment. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.IT (in descending order of likelihood).
